Information
------------------------------

Celebrating 30 years since Julius &quot;Dr. J&quot; Erving led the Philadelphia 76ers to the NBA championship, NBA TV Originals presents the new documentary, The Doctor, looking back at the life and career of one of game's greatest players. Through rare footage and original interviews, The Doctor shows how Erving reinvented basketball while playing in the American Basketball Association and how he later brought his above- the-rim artistry to the NBA. 
Many basketball fans were introduced to Erving when he joined the NBA at age 26, and what they saw was some of the most amazing aerial artistry in the game. What most didn't see, however, was the young Doctor, reinventing the sport during his five spectatular seasons in the ABA. Through rare archival footage, all aspects of Dr. J's career will come to life again in this documentary. Those who witnessed his greatness up close and personal include Pat Riley, Bob Costas, and Doug Collins speaking on their experiences watching him in the league. He brought us some of the biggest jaw-dropping highlights influencing many in the NBA from Michael Jordan to Vince Carter, and LeBron James. 
Along with his storied playing career, the film reveals the challenges Erving has faced off the court as he opens up for the first time about three tragedies and the impact on his life: the death of his father when he was only nine-years-old, his younger brother Marvin when he was 19-years-old, and his youngest son Cory after an automobile accident.

